h2></div></div><div class=\"grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3\"><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Lucky Number</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold text-slate-900\">7</p></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Lucky Day</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900\">Tuesday</p></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Lucky Colors</p><div class=\"mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2\"><span class=\"rounded-full bg-white px-3 py-1 text-sm text-slate-700 ring-1 ring-slate-200\">Yellow</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-white px-3 py-1 text-sm text-slate-700 ring-1 ring-slate-200\">Purple</span></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Lucky Stone</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900\">Olivine</p></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Life Path Number</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900\">3</p></div></div><div class=\"mt-4 rounded-3xl bg-amber-50 p-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\"><span class=\"font-semibold text-slate-900\">Numerology meaning:</span> <!-- -->People with a life path number 3 are often creative, passionate, and sociable. They have a natural talent for communication and self-expression.</div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-heart h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M2 9.5a5.5 5.5 0 0 1 9.591-3.676.56.56 0 0 0 .818 0A5.49 5.49 0 0 1 22 9.5c0 2.29-1.5 4-3 5.5l-5.492 5.313a2 2 0 0 1-3 .019L5 15c-1.5-1.5-3-3.2-3-5.5\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Personality</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Personality Traits</h2></div></div><div class=\"flex flex-wrap gap-2\"><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">Kind</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">Faithful</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">Courageous</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">L = Loyal</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">S = Strong</span></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-book-text h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2H19a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v18a1 1 0 0 1-1 1H6.5a1 1 0 0 1 0-5H20\"></path><path d=\"M8 11h8\"></path><path d=\"M8 7h6\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Spiritual</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Spiritual Significance</h2></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-amber-50 p-4 text-slate-800 leading-7\">Symbolizes peace, prosperity, and the presence of God.</div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-shield h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Cultural Context</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Cultural Significance</h2></div></div><div class=\"space-y-4 text-slate-700 leading-7\"><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4\">The name Oliver has become popular in many English-speaking countries due to William Makepeace Thackeray&#x27;s novel &quot;Vanity Fair,&quot; where the central character, Becky Sharp, marries a man named Oliver Dangl ses. Although it started as a male name, it has also been used for girls, especially in the United States.</div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4\">The name Oliver carries a deep spiritual significance as it is derived from the olive tree, a symbol of peace and the presence of God in the Bible. This name can serve as a reminder of the spiritual values we should hold dear, such as peace, prosperity, and God’s presence in our lives. It can be a daily inspiration to live in harmony with others and to remain connected to the divine.</div><p class=\"rounded-3xl bg-purple-50 p-4 text-sm text-purple-800\">Saint connection: <!-- -->Saint Oliver Plunkett<!-- --> — Saint Oliver Plunkett was an Irish martyr who was executed in 1681 for his faith. He is the patron saint of Ireland and is celebrated by the Catholic Church on July 1st.</p></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-clock h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"></circle><path d=\"M12 6v6l4 2\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Historical Usage</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Historical References</h2></div></div><div class=\"space-y-4\"><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\">Oliver Cromwell was a 17th century English military leader and political figure who served as Lord Protector of the Commonwealth of England, Scotland, and Ireland.</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">17th century</p></div></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-sparkles h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M11.017 2.814a1 1 0 0 1 1.966 0l1.051 5.558a2 2 0 0 0 1.594 1.594l5.558 1.051a1 1 0 0 1 0 1.966l-5.558 1.051a2 2 0 0 0-1.594 1.594l-1.051 5.558a1 1 0 0 1-1.966 0l-1.051-5.558a2 2 0 0 0-1.594-1.594l-5.558-1.051a1 1 0 0 1 0-1.966l5.558-1.051a2 2 0 0 0 1.594-1.594z\"></path><path d=\"M20 2v4\"></path><path d=\"M22 4h-4\"></path><circle cx=\"4\" cy=\"20\" r=\"2\"></circle></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Spiritual</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Spiritual Symbolism</h2></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-amber-50 p-4 text-slate-800 leading-7\">Oliver, derived from the Latin word &quot;olivus&quot; meaning olive tree, symbolizes peace, prosperity, and strength in the Christian tradition. The olive tree is a symbol of the peace offering in the Old Testament and represents the fruitfulness of the spirit in a believer&#x27;s life.</div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-trending-up h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M16 7h6v6\"></path><path d=\"m22 7-8.5 8.5-5-5L2 17\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Popularity</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Popularity by Region</h2></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4 text-slate-700 leading-7\"><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Spain</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->52</span></div><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">United States</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->40</span></div><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Germany</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->78</span></div></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-award h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m15.477 12.89 1.515 8.526a.5.5 0 0 1-.81.47l-3.58-2.687a1 1 0 0 0-1.197 0l-3.586 2.686a.5.5 0 0 1-.81-.469l1.514-8.526\"></path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"8\" r=\"6\"></circle></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Famous People</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Famous People and Real-World Usage</h2></div></div><p class=\"text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500 mb-3\">Historical Figures &amp; Cultural References</p><div class=\"flex flex-wrap gap-2\"><span class=\"rounded-2xl bg-slate-100 px-3 py-2 text-sm text-slate-700\">Oliver Twist (character)</span><span class=\"rounded-2xl bg-slate-100 px-3 py-2 text-sm text-slate-700\">Oliver Queen (Arrow)</span><span class=\"rounded-2xl bg-slate-100 px-3 py-2 text-sm text-slate-700\">Oliver Sacks (Neurologist)</span></div></section><section class=\"nv-card-solid\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-languages h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m5 8 6 6\"></path><path d=\"m4 14 6-6 2-3\"></path><path d=\"M2 5h12\"></path><path d=\"M7 2h1\"></path><path d=\"m22 22-5-10-5 10\"></path><path d=\"M14 18h6\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Translations</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Name Translations</h2><p class=\"mt-1 text-sm text-slate-500\">Additional language translations available for this name.</p></div></div><div class=\"grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2\"><div class=\"nv-card-solid p-4\"><div class=\"mb-2 flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900\"><span>🇺🇸</span><span>English</span></div><p class=\"font-semibold text-slate-900\">Oliver</p><p class=\"mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\">name derived from the Latin &#x27;oliva&#x27; meaning &#x27;olive tree&#x27; or &#x27;olive oil&#x27;</p></div><div class=\"nv-card-solid p-4\"><div class=\"mb-2 flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900\"><span>🇮🇱</span><span>Hebrew</span></div><p class=\"font-semibold text-slate-900\">עוליבר</p><p class=\"mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\">מוצא מאלפבאית יהודית לבית &#x27;אוליב&#x27; שמאוחר יותר התפתח</p></div><div class=\"nv-card-solid p-4\"><div class=\"mb-2 flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900\"><span>🇬🇷</span><span>Greek</span></div><p class=\"font-semibold text-slate-900\">Όλιβερ</p><p class=\"mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\">προέλευση από την ελληνική λέξη &#x27;ολύβρος&#x27; που σήμαινε &#x27;αφρός&#x27; ή &#x27;πλούσιο&#x27;</p></div><div class=\"nv-card-solid p-4\"><div class=\"mb-2 flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900\"><span>🇮🇹</span><span>Latin</span></div><p class=\"font-semibold text-slate-900\">Oliverius</p><p class=\"mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\">nomen gentile derivatum a vocabulo &#x27;oliva&#x27; quod significabit &#x27;oleum&#x27; aut &#x27;oliva&#x27;</p></div></div></section></div><section class=\"nv-card-solid\" aria-labelledby=\"similar-names-heading\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-center gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-10