l.app/names/christian/oliver#name-term\",\"name\":\"Oliver\",\"text\":\"Drives or olives\",\"description\":\"Oliver is a male name from Biblical origin, used in Christian contexts. It means Drives or olives. Pronunciation: OL-i-ver. Lucky number: 7.\",\"alternateName\":[\"עוליבר\",\"Όλιβερ\",\"Oliverius\"],\"additionalProperty\":[{\"@type\":\"PropertyValue\",\"name\":\"Origin\",\"value\":\"Biblical\"},{\"@type\":\"PropertyValue\",\"name\":\"Religion\",\"value\":\"Christian\"},{\"@type\":\"PropertyValue\",\"name\":\"Language\",\"value\":\"English, Hebrew, Greek, Latin\"},{\"@type\":\"PropertyValue\",\"name\":\"Gender\",\"value\":\"Male\"},{\"@type\":\"PropertyValue\",\"name\":\"Pronunciation\",\"value\":\"OL-i-ver\"},{\"@type\":\"PropertyValue\",\"name\":\"Lucky Number\",\"value\":\"7\"},{\"@type\":\"PropertyValue\",\"name\":\"Lucky Day\",\"value\":\"Tuesday\"},{\"@type\":\"PropertyValue\",\"name\":\"Lucky Colors\",\"value\":\"Yellow, Purple\"},{\"@type\":\"PropertyValue\",\"name\":\"Personality Traits\",\"value\":\"Kind, Faithful, Courageous, L = Loyal, S = Strong\"}]}41:[\"$\",\"$L3e\",null,{\"id\":\"definedterm-schema\",\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$47\"}}]\n48:T853,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"ScholarlyArticle\",\"@id\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/christian/oliver#scholarly-article\",\"headline\":\"Oliver — Name Meaning, Origin & Cultural Context | NameVerse\",\"name\":\"Oliver — Name Meaning and Origin\",\"description\":\"Name meaning and origin analysis for Oliver: Biblical origin, Christian context, pronunciation, lucky number, translations, personality traits, and cultural references.\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/christian/oliver\",\"image\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/logo.png\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-14\",\"dateModified\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"inLanguage\":\"en\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"@id\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/#organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\"},\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"@id\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/#organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\",\"description\":\"NameVerse is a cultural name knowledge base for name meanings, origins, pronunciation, lucky numbers, and naming context.\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\",\"logo\":{\"@type\":\"ImageObject\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/logo.png\",\"width\":512,\"height\":512},\"sameAs\":[\"https://twitter.com/NameVerseOfficial\",\"https://facebook.com/NameVerse\",\"https://instagram.com/nameverse\",\"https://linkedin.com/company/nameverse\"],\"foundingDate\":\"2025\",\"numberOfEmployees\":{\"@type\":\"QuantitativeValue\",\"minValue\":5,\"maxValue\":20},\"contactPoint\":{\"@type\":\"ContactPoint\",\"contactType\":\"customer support\",\"email\":\"hello@nameverse.com\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/contact\"}},\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/christian/oliver#webpage\"},\"about\":{\"@type\":\"DefinedTerm\",\"@id\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/christian/oliver#name-term\",\"name\":\"Oliver\",\"description\":\"Drives or olives\"},\"articleSection\":\"Name Meaning\",\"keywords\":\"Oliver meaning, Oliver origin, Biblical linguistics, Christian names, pronunciation, lucky number, cultural context\",\"wordCount\":500,\"citation\":{\"@type\":\"CreativeWork\",\"name\":\"NameVerse — Cultural Name Knowledge Base\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\"}}42:[\"$\",\"$L3e\",null,{\"id\":\"scholarly-article-schema\",\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$48\"}}]\n49:T1fb2,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What does Oliver mean?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Linguistically, Oliver conveys \\\"Drives or olives\\\" from its Biblical origin. The christian tradition preserves this boy name for its meaningful resonance across cultural boundaries.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the origin of the name Oliver?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Oliver traces its etymological roots to Biblical, with documented usage in English and Hebrew and Greek and Latin. This christian name reflects centuries of cross-cultural naming exchange.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Is Oliver a boy, girl, or unisex name?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The name Oliver is listed as Male in christian naming records. Parents should note that gender classification of names can differ by region and cultural context.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How do you pronounce Oliver?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Speakers pronounce Oliver as \\\"OL-i-ver\\\" (/ˈɒlɪvər/). This articulation maintains the Biblical sound structure while adapting to English phonetic conventions.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the phonetic transcription of Oliver?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Phonetically, Oliver is transcribed as /ˈɒlɪvər/. The IPA representation helps linguists and language learners capture the name's authentic Biblical pronunciation.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the lucky associations for Oliver?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"According to Biblical naming traditions, Oliver corresponds to lucky number 7, with Tuesday as the most fortunate day, colours Yellow and Purple, and Olivine as the lucky gemstone. These associations vary by cultural system.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the numerology of Oliver?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"In numerology, Oliver corresponds to the number 7, with Tuesday as a significant day, and Olivine as a related gemstone. Numerological analysis assigns meaning based on letter values and phonetic structure.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What personality traits are associated with Oliver?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Names like Oliver in christian tradition carry connotations of Kind, Faithful, Courageous, L = Loyal. These personality associations connect the name's meaning to expected character qualities.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the cultural significance of Oliver?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The cultural significance of Oliver stems from its Biblical roots and christian context. The name Oliver has become popular in many English-speaking countries due to William Makepeace Thackeray's novel \\\"Vanity Fair,\\\" where the central character, Becky Sharp, marries a man named Oliver Dangl ses. Although it started as a male name, it has also been used for girls, especially in the United States. The meaning \\\"Drives or olives\\\" reinforces the name's place in cultural naming practice.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the spiritual meaning of Oliver?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The spiritual dimension of Oliver extends beyond its surface meaning of \\\"Drives or olives\\\". Within christian thought, symbolizes peace, prosperity, and the presence of God.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What names are similar to Oliver?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Names related to Oliver include abeliel, Abijah, Adalyn, Adelaide, Adele, Adonella. These share Biblical linguistic roots and often carry comparable meanings or phonetic patterns.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What category does Oliver belong to?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The name Oliver falls under the \\\"Saint\\\" category within christian naming classifications. This categorisation helps parents find names that match their thematic preferences.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How is Oliver written in Hebrew?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Oliver appears in Hebrew as \\\"מוצא מאלפבאית יהודית לבית 'אוליב' שמאוחר יותר התפתח\\\". This adaptation preserves the name's essential character while conforming to hebrew orthographic rules.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How is Oliver written in Greek?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The Greek equivalent of Oliver is \\\"προέλευση από την ελληνική λέξη 'ολύβρος' που σήμαινε 'αφρός' ή 'πλούσιο'\\\". Such translations show how the name transcends linguistic boundaries while retaining its fundamental meaning.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How is Oliver written in Latin?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"In Latin, the name Oliver is written as \\\"nomen gentile derivatum a vocabulo 'oliva' quod significabit 'oleum' aut 'oliva'\\\". This rendering adapts the name's sound and meaning to latin script and phonetic conventions.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T04:50:20.794Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}}]}43:[\"$\",\"$L3e\",null,{\"id\":\"faq-schema\",\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$49\"}}]\n44:[\"$\",\"$L3e\",null,{\"id\":\"breadcrumb-schema\",\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Christian Names\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/religion/christian/1\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Oliver\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/christian/oliver\\\"}]}\"}}]\n45:[\"$\",\"main\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-page min-h-screen\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-container nv-section\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"nav\",null,{\"aria-label\":\"Breadcrumb\",\"className\":\"mb-6\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"ol\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-sm text-slate-500\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",\"/-0\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L18\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"className\":\"font-medium text-slate-600 transition-colors hover:text-slate-900\",\"children\":\"Home\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-slate-300\",\"children\":\"/\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"/names-1\",{\"className\":\"fl